Durban - A Clare Estate teenager died after he was hit by a car while walking to a church youth meeting on Saturday. Cole Calvin Kallee, 14, a Grade 9 pupil at Burnwood Secondary School sustained severe head injuries. He died soon after paramedics transported him to Addington Hospital. His aunt Sharon Kallee said the teen's death had left their family shattered. "He just left home to go to the youth meeting and has he was crossing O'Flaherty Road he was struck by a car. Residents from the area contacted the ambulance and he was transported to the hospital. His injuries, however, were too severe and he died." His parents, Shaun and Jenny, said Kallee was struggling to come to terms with his death and are expected to undergo counselling. "Cole was a lovely and respectful child. He had a bright future ahead of him and had dreams of becoming an architect. We are praying that we can get clarity in terms of what had happened on Saturday." She said his funeral will take place on Wednesday at the Believers Christian Church in Asherville. Police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane said a case of culpable homicide was opened at Sydenham SAPS. "It is alleged on November 10, 2018 at 1.30pm, a 14-year-old boy was crossing the road when he was struck by a vehicle. He sustained head injuries and was taken to hospital where he later died. " POST